[SN]TITLE[SN]
University of Bedfordshire student nurses train with dummies

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A simulation hospital complete with dummy patients has been set up at the University of Bedfordshire to train nurses.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
3 June 2015 Last updated at 20:45 BST
Students can follow every stage of a patient's care, from A&E to the operating theatre, and they work shifts to gain a true understanding of what it is like to work in a hospital.
Neil Bradford reports.
